Database migrations (Alembic, single database).

The database URL is not stored in alembic.ini. It is loaded at runtime from
application settings (POSTGRES_URL) by env.py, which also registers the models'
metadata (app.infrastructure.database.Base) as the autogenerate target.

Common commands (run from backend/):

    uv run alembic upgrade head              # apply all pending migrations
    uv run alembic downgrade -1              # roll back the latest migration
    uv run alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"
    uv run alembic current                   # show the applied revision
    uv run alembic history                   # list all revisions

After autogenerating a migration, review the generated file before committing:
adjust the upgrade/downgrade operations as needed and remove the
"auto generated by Alembic" marker comments.
